To terminate a C program, you can use the `exit()` function from the `stdlib.h` library. Here's an example of how to use it:

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {
    printf("Hello, World!\n");
    exit(EXIT_SUCCESS); // Terminate the program with a successful status
    printf("This line will not be executed"); // This line will not be executed
    return 0;
}
```

In this example, `exit(EXIT_SUCCESS)` is used to terminate the program with a successful status. You can also use `exit(EXIT_FAILURE)` to terminate the program with a failure status.

